The dictionary data (dictionary.tsv) is derived from the following
open-source word frequency lists and is distributed under the
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License
(CC BY-SA 4.0).

License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

Sources
-------

1. CAMeL Arabic Frequency Lists (MIX)
   License: CC BY-SA 4.0
   URL: https://github.com/CAMeL-Lab/Camel_Arabic_Frequency_Lists
   Data: Combined Classical, Dialectal, and Modern Standard Arabic
         frequency lists from CAMeLBERT pretraining data (17.3B tokens).

   Citation (required by license):
   Go Inoue, Bashar Alhafni, Nurpeiis Baimukan, Houda Bouamor, and
   Nizar Habash. 2021. The Interplay of Variant, Size, and Task Type
   in Arabic Pre-trained Language Models. In Proceedings of the Sixth
   Arabic Natural Language Processing Workshop, pages 92-104, Kyiv,
   Ukraine (Virtual). Association for Computational Linguistics.

2. FrequencyWords (OpenSubtitles 2018)
   License: MIT
   URL: https://github.com/hermitdave/FrequencyWords
   Data: Arabic word frequencies from OpenSubtitles 2018 corpus.

3. Wikipedia Word Frequency
   License: MIT
   URL: https://github.com/IlyaSemenov/wikipedia-word-frequency
   Data: Arabic word frequencies from Arabic Wikipedia (2022-08-29 dump).

Build Process
-------------

The dictionary is built by scripts/build_dictionary.py which:
- Includes words appearing in 2+ of the above sources (cross-validated)
- Includes single-source words with raw frequency >= 1000
- Auto-generates taa marbuta variants (ة/ه) for IME coverage
- Normalizes combined frequencies to a 1-10000 scale

To reproduce:
  See scripts/build_dictionary.py for full instructions.
